<br>
Promises were made via marketing materials, posts at the EQ site, etc. that portrayed the game in a certain fashion - one which a  considerable majority feel has yet to be realized. For some time now, many have preferred to take a 'wait and see' perspective and that's really very commendable. <br>
<br>
Unfortunately, Verant and Sony Online Entertainment have taken a fairly nonchalant view of complaints and an all but non-existant interest in actually providing the level of service and interactivity (i.e., events, etc.) they promised would be an integral component of this product. <br>
<br>
This has but contributed to the underlying dissatisfaction of their customers and the latest news of the product people *thought* they were going to be receiving arriving with additional fees is considered by many to be a slap in the face... perhaps even the last straw.<br>
<br>
I have been surprised people haven't pursued the matter in a more logical and effective way. Perhaps this is the beginning of something along those lines. Personally, I believe there is a case to be made that EQ has failed rather significantly to deliver the product promised to its customers. <br>
<br>
Is anyone interested in making such a case? I become more and more interested in doing so. Not because I hold any personal vendetta against Verant or Sony Online... but because I believe it is inherently wrong to allow a company to get away with 'bait and switch' tactics, and in my personal opinion - that is precisely what has occurred.<br>
<br>
