<br>
Now we see that while they couldn't implement a great deal of what they were promising with SoL, they DID have time to code new interfaces, and add features to the game that we paid for, but will never see.  We see that the content and service that we were promised when EQ went live, and arguably have yet to see, is available for an extra thirty bones a month?!  I don't know who coined it, but the sentiment seems to be:<br>
<br>
&quot;You're in our world now, and the rent just went up.&quot;<br>
<br>
Meanwhile, I'm having fun with Everquest, and will continue to, but I'm not paying any more for the service than I am now.  If'n I ever feel that the level of service I'm rendered isn't worth what I'm paying for it I'll just stop playing.  I don't have any shares in Sony stock, so I don't care what they do with the money I send them for EQ.  I would, however, like to see them finish the product I bought afore they start making new'uns. <p><img src="http://web4.facelink.com/edit/raw/rawimage/39/2383739.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/uarkusebonblade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Arkus Ebonblade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Scowling Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(2/3/02 12:29:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=395.topic&index=29>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://darkretribution.homestead.com/files/hobs_anm.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_mad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: EQ Legends servers.</span><hr size=1> Just wanted to comment on Verant's answers to some concerns about the Legends server up at EQ Casters Realm<br>
